# Handoff — Pack #5 (Knowledge Engine) Phase 2 complete

## What was done

**Phase 2 (Read path) of Pack #5
(`knowledge-engine-json-store`) is
code-complete.** The full read path is
implemented end-to-end: `find_information`
does topic + tag + free-text scoring with
proper locking discipline, and `list_topics`
returns the per-topic summaries sorted by
name. The conformance suite is now full (not
a stub) — `MockAdapter` plus per-method cases
for `store_information`, `find_information`,
and `list_topics` in `afa-knowledge`. A new
`KnowledgeTopicsListed` audit event was added
to the contracts.

## Key bug found and fixed this session

`find_information` held the index read lock
across the call to `search::filter_and_score`,
which dispatched the content-token loader that
tried to upgrade to the write lock — a
classic read→write lock deadlock. The free-text
test (`phase2_find_information_free_text_ranks_by_overlap`)
hung indefinitely. The fix inlined the
filter+score logic into `find_information`:
snapshot the candidate set and the cached
tokens under a brief read lock, release the
lock, await the loader (which takes its own
short read+write locks for the cache write),
then re-read the cache briefly. Net result:
no lock held across any await on the loader.

`list_topics` was also a stub returning
`CapabilityUnsupported` — replaced with the
real implementation that calls
`index.all_topic_summaries()` and publishes
the `KnowledgeTopicsListed` event.

